first_reading.text:
[[2_Co 6,1]]Brothers and sisters: As your fellow workers, we appeal to you not to receive the grace of God in vain.
[[2_Co 6,2]]For he says: "In an acceptable time I heard you, and on the day of salvation I helped you." Behold, now is a very acceptable time; behold, now is the day of salvation.
[[2_Co 6,3]]We cause no one to stumble in anything, in order that no fault may be found with our ministry;
[[2_Co 6,4]]on the contrary, in everything we commend ourselves as ministers of God, through much endurance, in afflictions, hardships, constraints,
[[2_Co 6,5]]beatings, imprisonments, riots, labors, vigils, fasts;
[[2_Co 6,6]]by purity, knowledge, patience, kindness, in a holy spirit, in unfeigned love,
[[2_Co 6,7]]in truthful speech, in the power of God; with weapons of righteousness at the right and at the left;
[[2_Co 6,8]]through glory and dishonor, insult and praise. We are treated as deceivers and yet are truthful;
[[2_Co 6,9]]as unrecognized and yet acknowledged; as dying and behold we live; as chastised and yet not put to death;
[[2_Co 6,10]]as sorrowful yet always rejoicing; as poor yet enriching many; as having nothing and yet possessing all things.
